{"state":"florida","state_code":"FL","family":"county_local_disability_resources","family_status":"blocked_official_storefront_root_and_csv_only_cover_partial_county_set_and_authenticated_myaccess_results","evidence_strength":"medium","sample_count":11,"query_basis":"Reviewed 2026-06-23 the official DCF public-assistance leaves, Family Resource Center root and CSV, and one more bounded MyACCESS config/shell pass.","blocker_code":"official_family_resource_center_html_and_csv_both_materialize_only_partial_county_contract_while_myaccess_results_stay_authenticated","blocker_evidence":"Reviewed 2026-06-23 one more bounded official Florida county-local pass on the first-party storefront and MyACCESS config shell. The Family Resource Center root at https://familyresourcecenter.myflfamilies.com/ remains live and `providers.csv` still preserves only 34 distinct county values across 39 rows rather than a 67-county contract. On the MyACCESS side, https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/config/appconfig.js still wires the search services through `/accountmanagement`, including the county-result lanes already probed anonymously. Meanwhile https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/config/config.json, https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/swagger, and https://myaccess.myflfamilies.com/swagger/index.html all return only the same generic SPA shell rather than a public API description or alternate anonymous result surface. Florida therefore remains blocked because the readable storefront lane is partial and the MyACCESS county-result lane still has no public anonymous contract.","samples":[{"sample_name":"Florida Food Cash and Medical","source_url":"https://www.myflfamilies.com/food-cash-and-medical","final_url":"https://www.myflfamilies.com/food-cash-and-medical","verification_status":"reviewed","source_type":"official_local_offices_leaf_to_partial_storefront_lane","source_table":"batch275_florida_storefront_county_contract_finality","fetched_at":"2026-06-23T00:00:00.000Z","evidence_snippet":"The pag